{{unindent}}We need to consider how other encyclopedias handle this situation. ''Britannica'', which uses British English, regardless always disambiguates which code is meant. [[Pele]] is a [http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/449124/Pele "football (soccer) player"]. Same for [[David Beckham]][http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/760149/David-Beckham]. American player [[Mia Hamm]] is also a [http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/253562/Mia-Hamm "football (soccer) player"]. On the other hand [[Dan Marino]] is a [http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/1382038/Dan-Marino "gridiron football player]", and the [[Jacksonville Jaguars]] are a "[http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/1710505/Jacksonville-Jaguars "professional gridiron football team"] (Britannica doesn't have separate articles on American and Canadian football; they are both discussed under [[gridiron football]]). The American ''[[Columbia Encyclopedia]]'' also distinguishes the sports, though using the American standard. Pele is a [http://www.encyclopedia.com/topic/Pele_%28soccer_player%29.aspx "Brazilian soccer (football) player"] while Beckham is an [http://www.encyclopedia.com/topic/David_Beckham.aspx "English soccer player"] and Hamm is a [http://www.encyclopedia.com/topic/Mia_Hamm.aspx#1E1-HammMia "U.S. soccer player"]. Dan Marino is an [http://www.encyclopedia.com/doc/1E1-MarinoDn.html "American football player"] as is [[John Elway]][http://www.encyclopedia.com/doc/1E1-ElwayJ.html] and others.<br>
These two encyclopedias clearly make a conscious effort to distinguish which type of football is being referred to, and don't refer to any one sport as "football" without disambiguating it in the text. I suppose one could argue that in ''Columbia'', it is Marino, Elway, et al who are "American" and the sport is being referred to as "football", but it's really immaterial since they are both U.S. citizens and play what Columbia calls "American football". Additionally Mia Hamm, the only American soccer player to have an article, is called a "U.S. soccer player" rather than "American soccer player". The only player of any type of football besides soccer and American to have an article is [[Warren Moon]]; he played Canadian football for several years, but was actually American and played in the National Football League too. Columbia calls him an [http://www.encyclopedia.com/doc/1E1-MoonWarn.html "African-American football player"] and then refers to the leagues he played in.--[[User:Cuchullain|Cúchullain]] [[User talk:Cuchullain|<sup>t</sup>]]/[[Special:Contributions/Cuchullain|<small>c</small>]] 15:46, 29 September 2010 (UTC)
